        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30152",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bittarman",
                        "name": "bittarman",
                        "displayName": "Ryan Mauger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Patch for Zend_Controller_Action",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bittarman",
                        "name": "bittarman",
                        "displayName": "Ryan Mauger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-04-15T10:25:48.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-04-15T10:25:48.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30154",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dasprid",
                        "name": "dasprid",
                        "displayName": "Ben Scholzen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The validation of the route-parameters should usually be done with the \"reqs\"-param of the routes. Suggesting WONTFIX.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dasprid",
                        "name": "dasprid",
                        "displayName": "Ben Scholzen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-04-15T11:20:55.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-04-15T11:20:55.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30155",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bittarman",
                        "name": "bittarman",
                        "displayName": "Ryan Mauger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I disagree, in order to use the \"reqs\" param, you need to add a route. This will obviously not work with the default routes.\nIf I add a route for every time I needed paramaters in the URL i'd end up with a few hundred routes in every app just to deal with this.\nI don't always want to add a route to add parameters to an action.\nAlso _getParams can be used for $_GET and $_POST paramaters, (if you set the param sources to allow it), which obviously a route would not be able to validate.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bittarman",
                        "name": "bittarman",
                        "displayName": "Ryan Mauger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-04-15T11:39:14.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-04-15T11:39:14.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30157",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This is basically a poor man's poka-yoke. I like the idea, but it's the wrong location -- this should be in the request object, not the action controller.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-04-15T12:27:51.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-04-15T12:27:51.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30158",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sgehrig",
                        "name": "sgehrig",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Gehrig",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Nice idea. +1\n\nPerhaps you can even think of injecting both a validator (could be a validator-chain) and a filter (could be a filter-chain).",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sgehrig",
                        "name": "sgehrig",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Gehrig",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-04-15T12:29:11.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-04-15T12:29:11.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30160",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dasprid",
                        "name": "dasprid",
                        "displayName": "Ben Scholzen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This improvement should base on a proposal, as filtering may another part of this. Our current idea for layout of _getParam() is, that it proxied to getParam() of the request object with the following method signature:\n\n_getParam($param, $default, array('validator' => ..., 'filter' => ...));",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dasprid",
                        "name": "dasprid",
                        "displayName": "Ben Scholzen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-04-15T12:43:03.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-04-15T12:43:03.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30161",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bittarman",
                        "name": "bittarman",
                        "displayName": "Ryan Mauger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "There is now a proposal for this @ http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/wiki\/display\/ZFPROP\/Zend_Controller_Request+-+Add+validation+and+filtering+to+getParam%28%29\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bittarman",
                        "name": "bittarman",
                        "displayName": "Ryan Mauger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-04-15T13:41:19.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-04-15T13:41:19.000+0000"
                },
                {
